#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:1
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:3
msgid ""
"Terms are defined as they are used in the cuda-oxide project and this book."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:7
msgid "ABI Scalarization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:9
msgid ""
"The process of decomposing composite types into a shape both host and device "
"agree on. Slices flatten at all call boundaries: `&[T]` becomes a `(ptr, "
"len)` pair, reconstructed inside the function via `insertvalue`/"
"`extractvalue`. Structs and closures by value flatten the same way for "
"internal device-to-device calls, but at the **kernel** boundary they instead "
"travel as one byval `.param` (one host packet slot) â€” that matches what the "
"host launcher pushes and avoids mismatches between flattened device "
"declarations and a single-slot host packet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:19
msgid "Block (Thread Block)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:21
msgid ""
"A group of threads that execute on the same Streaming Multiprocessor and "
"share access to shared memory. Threads within a block can synchronize via "
"`sync_threads()`. Identified by `blockIdx` and sized by `blockDim`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:25
msgid "Cluster (Thread Block Cluster)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:27
msgid ""
"A Hopper+ (sm_90) feature: a group of up to 16 thread blocks guaranteed to "
"be co-scheduled on the same GPC. Blocks in a cluster can access each other's "
"shared memory via Distributed Shared Memory (DSMEM) and synchronize via "
"`cluster_sync()`. Configured with `#[cluster_launch]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:32
msgid "Codegen Backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:34
msgid ""
"The `rustc_codegen_cuda` crate â€” a custom rustc backend loaded as a dylib. "
"It intercepts MIR during compilation, lowers it through `dialect-mir` â†’ "
"`mem2reg` â†’ annotated loop unroll â†’ LLVM dialect â†’ LLVM IR â†’ PTX. It emits "
"PTX alongside the normal host binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:39
msgid "`cuda-async`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:41
msgid ""
"The async execution layer. Provides `DeviceOperation` (lazy GPU work "
"description), `DeviceFuture` (stream-bound execution), and `DeviceBox<T>` "
"(device-owned memory). Compose work with `zip!`, `and_then`, and `value()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:45
msgid "`cuda-device`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:47
msgid ""
"The `#![no_std]` device-side crate providing all GPU intrinsics and types: "
"thread identification, shared memory, warp primitives, barriers, TMA, tensor "
"cores, atomics, and debug facilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:51
msgid "`cuda-core`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:53
msgid ""
"Safe RAII wrappers around the CUDA Driver API: `CudaContext`, `CudaStream`, "
"`DeviceBuffer<T>`, and module loading. Handles GPU context and memory "
"management on the host side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:57
msgid "`DeviceOperation`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:59
msgid ""
"A lazy, composable description of GPU work (allocation, kernel launch, or "
"data transfer). Not executed until `.sync()` or `.await` is called. Can be "
"combined with `zip!` (parallel) and `and_then` (sequential)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:63
msgid "`DisjointSlice<T, IndexSpace>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:65
msgid ""
"A safe mutable output abstraction for kernels. Accepts only a `ThreadIndex` "
"whose `IndexSpace` matches its own type parameter, providing bounds-checked "
"`Option<&mut T>` returns. With matching prepared launch geometry, each "
"thread can only write to its own element. The `get_mut_indexed()` shortcut "
"mints the witness and resolves it to a mutable reference in a single call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:72
msgid "Distributed Shared Memory (DSMEM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:74
msgid ""
"A Hopper+ feature allowing blocks within a cluster to read and write each "
"other's shared memory directly, without going through global memory. "
"Accessed via `cluster::map_shared_rank()` to translate local shared pointers "
"to remote addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:79
msgid "Grid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:81
msgid ""
"The top-level organization of threads in a kernel launch. A grid is a 3-"
"dimensional array of thread blocks, sized by `gridDim`. The total number of "
"threads is `gridDim Ă— blockDim`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:85
msgid "HMM (Heterogeneous Memory Management)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:87
msgid ""
"A Linux kernel feature (6.1.24+) that lets the GPU access host memory "
"directly through page faults, without explicit `cudaMemcpy`. cuda-oxide "
"leverages HMM for reference captures in closures â€” the GPU reads host "
"addresses transparently. Also called Unified Memory Management (UMM)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:92
msgid "Lane"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:94
msgid ""
"A single thread within a warp. Lanes are numbered 0â€“31 and identified by "
"`warp::lane_id()`. Warp shuffle and vote operations communicate between "
"lanes without shared memory or barriers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:98
msgid "LTOIR (Link-Time Optimized IR)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:100
msgid ""
"An intermediate representation used for device-side link-time optimization. "
"cuda-oxide emits NVVM IR for libNVVM, which can compile it to LTOIR for "
"linking Rust device code with CUDA C++ device code using `nvJitLink`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:104
msgid "`ManagedBarrier<State, Kind, ID>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:106
msgid ""
"A typestate barrier for async operations on Hopper+. Tracks its lifecycle at "
"compile time (`Uninit â†’ Ready â†’ Invalidated`) and its purpose (`TmaBarrier`, "
"`MmaBarrier`, `GeneralBarrier`). Invalid state transitions are compile "
"errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:110
msgid "Monomorphization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:112
msgid ""
"The process by which the Rust compiler generates specialized copies of "
"generic functions for each concrete type used. cuda-oxide fully supports "
"monomorphization on device â€” `scale::<f32>` and `scale::<f64>` each become "
"separate PTX functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:117
msgid "`PreparedLaunch<K>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:119
msgid ""
"A reusable host-side proof that a launch configuration was checked for the "
"exact kernel `K`. Generated safe methods accept this branded value. Passing "
"a raw `LaunchConfig` directly to a generated method is instead unsafe "
"because it does not prove the kernel's indexing or resource requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:124
msgid "Pliron"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:126
msgid ""
"An MLIR-inspired IR framework written in Rust, used as the intermediate "
"representation in the cuda-oxide compilation pipeline. MIR is imported into "
"Pliron IR, transformed through dialect passes, and exported as LLVM IR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:130
msgid "PTX (Parallel Thread Execution)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:132
msgid ""
"NVIDIA's low-level virtual ISA for GPU kernels. The cuda-oxide compiler "
"emits PTX as its primary output, which the CUDA driver JIT-compiles to "
"native GPU machine code (SASS) at load time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:136
msgid "`SharedArray<T, N, ALIGN>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:138
msgid ""
"A compile-time sized, block-scoped shared memory array. Declared as `static "
"mut` in kernel functions. Optional alignment parameter (use `ALIGN=128` for "
"TMA destinations). Access requires `unsafe` because shared memory is `!Sync`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:142
msgid "SM (Streaming Multiprocessor)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:144
msgid ""
"The primary processing unit on an NVIDIA GPU. Each SM has its own registers, "
"shared memory, warp schedulers, and execution pipelines including Tensor "
"Cores. Thread blocks are scheduled onto SMs by the hardware scheduler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:148
msgid "`sync_threads()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:150
msgid ""
"The block-level barrier: all threads in the thread block must reach this "
"point before any thread proceeds past it. Equivalent to `__syncthreads()` in "
"CUDA C++. Lowers to `llvm.nvvm.barrier0()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:154
msgid "Tensor Cores"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:156
msgid ""
"Specialized matrix multiply-accumulate hardware units. WGMMA (Hopper, sm_90) "
"operates at warpgroup granularity from shared memory. tcgen05 (Blackwell, "
"sm_100+) uses single-thread issue with dedicated Tensor Memory (TMEM)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:160
msgid "`ThreadIndex<'kernel, IndexSpace>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:162
msgid ""
"An opaque witness that can only be constructed by trusted index functions. "
"Three forms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:165
msgid ""
"`thread::index_1d() -> ThreadIndex<'_, Index1D>`. Always returns a witness. "
"It is unique only when block and grid Y/Z dimensions are 1; a `domain = 1` "
"prepared launch proves this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:168
msgid ""
"`thread::index_2d::<S>() -> Option<ThreadIndex<'_, Index2D<S>>>`. The row "
"stride is a const generic, so a `DisjointSlice<T, Index2D<S>>` only accepts "
"a witness with the matching `S` -- mixing strides is a type error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:172
msgid ""
"`unsafe thread::index_2d_runtime(s) -> Option<ThreadIndex<'_, "
"Runtime2DIndex>>`. Escape hatch when the stride is only known at launch "
"time. The `unsafe` is the contract: every thread feeding a `Runtime2DIndex` "
"into the same `DisjointSlice` must have used the same `s`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:177
msgid ""
"The witness is `!Send + !Sync + !Copy + !Clone` and `'kernel`-scoped, so "
"threads cannot launder it through shared memory and it cannot outlive the "
"kernel body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:181
msgid "TMA (Tensor Memory Accelerator)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:183
msgid ""
"Hopper+ hardware unit for asynchronous bulk copies between global and shared "
"memory. Operates via `TmaDescriptor` (128-byte opaque descriptor built on "
"host) and `cp_async_bulk_tensor_*` intrinsics. Completion tracked by "
"`ManagedBarrier`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:187
msgid "`TmemGuard<State, N_COLS>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:189
msgid ""
"A typestate wrapper for Blackwell Tensor Memory (TMEM) â€” dedicated "
"accumulator storage for tcgen05 MMA operations. Manages TMEM lifetime: "
"`TmemUninit â†’ TmemReady â†’ TmemDeallocated`. Invalid transitions are compile "
"errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:194
msgid "Warp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:196
msgid ""
"A group of 32 threads that execute instructions in lockstep on an SM. Warps "
"are the smallest scheduling unit. Warp-level operations (shuffle, vote) "
"exchange data between lanes in ~1 cycle without shared memory or "
"synchronization barriers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:200
msgid "Warpgroup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:202
msgid ""
"Four consecutive warps (128 threads) that operate collectively for WGMMA "
"operations on Hopper. The warpgroup is the issuing unit for warpgroup-level "
"matrix multiply-accumulate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:206
msgid "WGMMA (Warpgroup Matrix Multiply-Accumulate)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../appendix/glossary.md:208
msgid ""
"The Hopper (sm_90) tensor core instruction set. Four warps collectively "
"issue MMA from shared memory operands into register accumulators. "
"Asynchronous execution with commit/wait via `ManagedBarrier`."
msgstr ""
